---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import HeadingSmall from "@components/HeadingSmall.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Rainforest | Work | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer & Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Rainforest</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Rainforest QA builds developer tools that help teams ship with confidence
      by blending no-code testing with an on-demand network of QA experts.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I joined as Product Design Lead and soon after became Director of Design,
      helping the company make the leap from a crowd-testing service to a
      product-led platform that engineering teams could adopt and scale on their
      own.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Partnering with the CEO, CPO, and Head of Marketing, I owned the end-to-end
      experience from brand to product. I guided our brand designer and product
      team to ensure Rainforest could speak credibly to developers while
      simplifying how customers created, ran, and collaborated on tests.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Brand and Positioning</Heading>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Design System</HeadingSmall>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Rainforest's product and marketing sites had grown separately, creating a
      split identity and inconsistent tone. I led a brand refresh that unified
      illustration, typography, and motion across every touchpoint.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The refreshed identity framed Rainforest as a dependable engineering tool
      rather than a services company, while still celebrating the human QA
      network that differentiated us from purely automated competitors.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/rainforest-branding-logo.png"
      alt="Rainforest QA wordmark and logomark refreshed for the product-led brand."
      width={3840}
      height={2560}
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The new system aligned web, app, and sales collateral, reducing design and
      engineering handoff time while giving Marketing a clearer story to tell
      about the hybrid automation-plus-humans model.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Test Authoring</HeadingSmall>
    <Text class="px-2">
      To serve teams without dedicated QA engineers, we needed a faster path
      from idea to executable test. I redesigned the authoring flow around
      real-time feedback, inline documentation, and reusable components so
      product managers could assemble reliable tests without code.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The streamlined experience reduced time-to-first-test and gave engineers
      higher confidence that non-technical contributors were creating maintainable
      suites, not one-off scripts that would break quietly.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/rainforest-test-authoring.png"
      alt="Rainforest QA no-code test authoring interface with reusable steps."
      width={3840}
      height={2560}
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Developer Workflows</HeadingSmall>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Beyond no-code creation, we met developers where they worked. I designed
      GitHub pull request checks, CLI output, and Slack notifications that made
      test results actionable inside existing workflows.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      By tightening the loop between authoring and debugging, engineering teams
      could keep test suites healthy without having to context-switch into a
      separate dashboard.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      These integrations increased product-qualified signups and helped the
      sales team demo the speed of Rainforest within a developer's familiar tool
      chain, improving conversion from trials to paid plans.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Results</HeadingSmall>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The combined brand and product work repositioned Rainforest as a modern QA
      platform. We shortened onboarding, improved activation, and equipped the
      go-to-market team with a coherent story that resonated with engineering
      leaders.
    </Text>
  </Group>
</Layout>
